3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Gate.io implements funding rate settlements every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC for FET/USDT perpetuals. Funding rates fluctuate based on the 8-hour time-weighted average price (TWAP) difference between the perpetual and spot markets. When the perpetual trades above spot, long positions pay shorts, and vice versa. Gate.io caps funding rates at ±0.75% per settlement to prevent extreme scenarios."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FET","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET/USDT represents the AI token narrative with sufficient liquidity for funding arbitrage while avoiding the extreme volatility of micro-cap alternatives. The pair's moderate volume on Gate.io creates opportunities for persistent funding rate imbalances during AI sector momentum. Gate.io's broad token coverage ensures FET perpetuals remain active even during low market interest periods."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET/USDT funding rates on Gate.io typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with spikes during AI narrative cycles reaching +0.5%. The pair exhibits positive funding bias during broader crypto rallies when retail interest flows into AI tokens. Weekend periods often show reduced funding premiums due to lower trading activity. Historical data indicates funding rates correlate strongly with FET's spot price momentum, creating predictable arbitrage windows during trend reversals."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Gate.io's FET/USDT pair offers arbitrage potential through spot-perp hedging during funding rate extremes above ±0.2%. The exchange's 0.015% maker rebate on spot trades enhances profitability when delta-hedging perpetual positions. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes viable when Gate.io's FET funding diverges significantly from Binance or OKX rates. Optimal position sizing ranges from $10k-$50k to avoid impacting the orderbook while capturing meaningful funding payments."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's moderate liquidity on Gate.io creates slippage risks during rapid market moves, particularly affecting larger arbitrage positions. The AI token sector's high correlation during narrative shifts can eliminate funding arbitrage opportunities across exchanges simultaneously. Gate.io's withdrawal processing times may impact cross-exchange strategies during volatile periods. Funding rate predictions become unreliable during major AI announcements or broader market stress, requiring dynamic position management and stop-loss protocols."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical FET/USDT funding rates on Gate.io?","answer":"FET/USDT funding rates on Gate.io typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour settlement, with occasional spikes to ±0.5% during AI sector momentum. The pair generally maintains positive funding bias during bull markets when retail interest drives perpetual premiums."},{"question":"How does Gate.io's 8-hour funding cycle affect FET arbitrage?","answer":"Gate.io's 8-hour funding settlements at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC provide three daily arbitrage opportunities for FET/USDT. The longer intervals compared to 1-hour cycles allow for more predictable rate accumulation but require careful timing around settlement periods."},{"question":"What position sizes work best for FET funding arbitrage on Gate.io?","answer":"Optimal FET/USDT arbitrage positions range from $10k-$50k on Gate.io to balance funding returns with slippage costs. Larger positions may face execution challenges due to moderate orderbook depth, while smaller amounts struggle to overcome the 0.05% taker fees effectively."},{"question":"How does FET's AI token classification impact funding rates?","answer":"FET's AI token status creates narrative-driven funding volatility, with rates spiking during AI sector rallies as retail traders pile into perpetuals. This correlation with broader AI token movements provides arbitrage opportunities but also increases unpredictability during sector rotations or major AI announcements."}]}]
